Weather API
Overview
A scalable and secure Node.js Weather API providing real-time weather data based on location and city search.

Features
Fetch weather by latitude and longitude.
Fetch weather by city name.
Redis caching for performance.
Rate limiting for security.
JWT authentication for user management.
64-bit AES encryption for responses.
Horizontal scaling with PM2 and Docker.
Swagger

Build and Run

npm run build
npm start

For development:
npm run dev


API Endpoints

POST	/api/auth/register	Register a user
POST	/api/auth/login	Authenticate user

GET	/api/weather/current?lat=40.7128&lon=-74.0060	Get weather by coordinates
GET	/api/weather/city/London	Get weather by city name


Run with Docker

docker-compose up --build -d


Swagger API Docs

http://localhost:5000/api-docs

